        "subtitle": "The Flagship Blade of Any Serious Kitchen",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Damascus chef knife</strong> is the centrepiece of any serious kitchen knife collection. XinZuo Damascus chef knives combine a 10Cr15CoMoV high-carbon cutting core with 67 layers of folded steel, creating a blade that is hard enough to hold a keen edge but flexible enough to handle the demands of daily kitchen work. Every blade is forged in Yangjiang by craftsmen who have been making knives for generations, using techniques passed down through decades of blade making. The 8-inch gyuto profile is the most versatile choice in the Damascus chef knife range, handling everything from dicing onions to breaking down a whole chicken with equal precision. Each blade features a unique Damascus wave pattern that develops character over time as you use it. Our <strong>kitchen knives</strong> are available in multiple handle materials including ebony, rosewood, and resin, so you can match your Damascus chef knife to your personal style and grip preference.</p>",
